definitions.definition: ( obsolete ) An administrative division of the county of Kent , in England, from the Anglo-Saxon period until it fell entirely out of use in the early twentieth century.

definitions.definition: A machine tool used to shape a piece of material, or workpiece , by rotating the workpiece against a cutting tool .
The movable swing frame of a loom , carrying the reed for separating the warp threads and beating up the weft .

main_definition: ( tools , metalworking , woodworking ) A machine tool used to shape a piece of material, or workpiece , by rotating the workpiece against a cutting tool .
